<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Background-color set to rgb() using percentages with a nominal value and a plus sign, rgb(+50%, +50%, +50%)</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/colors.html#propdef-background-color" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/colors.html#background-properties" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Background-color is set to rgb(+50%, +50%, +50%)." />
        <style type="text/css">
            img,#test
            {
                height: 1in;
                width: 1in;
            }
            #test
            {
                background-color: rgb(+50%, +50%, +50%);
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there are 2 squares with the <strong>same color</strong>.</p>
        <div id="test"></div>
        <div id="reference">
            <br />
            <img alt="#7f7f7f color swatch" src="support/7f7f7f_color.png" />
        </div>
    </body>
</html>